After the tragic loss of Norco (see related link) there are bound to be some changes in how things work around here. As it happens, Norco left control of this message board to me in his Last Will and Testament. Nice of him eh?<br>
But dont worry, to celebrate the Life and Times of Norco, I am throwing a huge bash. THE OPENING OF HEAVYHAND.ORG!!!!<br>
You heard me right, the HH now has its own website!!! Holy Cow you say?!?! Yes I say!!<br>
<br>
Change your links, and go directly to <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.HeavyHand.org,">www.HeavyHand.org,</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> it has links to this page so dont worry!<br>
<br>
Now for the changes. <br>
First, this board is for more than just a few EQ players. Its for all of us that make up the Heavy Hand and all of our friends from EQ, AO, GW, DAoC, and wherever else we may make friends (like the Quicky Mart). Because of this, EQ Names for accounts will NO LONGER be allowed excepted on this message board for the following reasons:<br>
A. You are a friend of the Heavy Hand (i.e. Legions of the Chosen). You are more than welcome to keep your name as is so that we may easily identify you and so that you my remain anon and not be directly linked to us and our organization. Realy, I dont blame you.<br>
B. You notify me by email (magikpants@heavyhand.org) within the next 14 days. EQ names can be kept, if that is now your internet identity. <br>
Thus, on October 12, all non approved names will be banned from posting. Sorry, but that is the way that it is.<br>
<br>
Second, I have a limited email addresses available at yourname@HH.org!!<br>
Now since I purchased a limited number of email accounts, they will be handed out to the following:<br>
A. People who are actively involved with production of the HH.org site. <br>
B. People who have contributed to the Community Chest here at Eazyboard so that we may remain advertising free.<br>
C. People who allow me to chain them to my bed post and to do anything that my evil heart disires.<br>
<br>
Now I know that may sound harsh and that some of the &quot;faithful&quot; may not get an email. Here it is as simply as I can put it. It comes down to money. I bought as many emails as I could afford. You want yours, then cough up the benjamins. Sorry, but the man is holding us down.<br>
<br>
Thirdly. We need images and input from everyone to make HH.org the most kick ass site for people with serious psychologic disorders (us). A new forum has been started to discuss those very things. If you have any pictures, stories, or proof that Squeeky is an alien, then send it to us at newmutant@heavyhand.org or magikpants@heavyhand.org .<br>
You wont be sorry.<br>
<br>
